race.comment: INQUISITOR (5) has switched from the Waller yard in Victoria. He was last seen a month ago beaten 3.4L over 1240m at Geelong. He's placed in the Flemington jumpout prior. Has some issues as he bucked two back, but has also shown talent. Looks the one to beat if he can keep his mind on the job. SECRET SCOUT (2) debuted here and was immediately tipped out. Resumes with two trials under the saddle and Anthony Allen booked. Has the rail and he can come back improved. SAMURAI WAND (6) was in the firing line on the corner when narrowly beaten here over 1540m. He can't be ruled out coming back to a sprint. ARIYAH (4) can improve for the Bruce yard and is in the mix.
